Pollution is when something is added to the environment that is harmful or poisonous to living things. Smoke in the air from factories is a type of pollution as it is bad for the lungs when breathed in. Sewage in drinking water is another type of pollution, as it can make people ill because it contains germs and viruses. People living next to a building site where there is too much noise can become sick as they cannot sleep or relax.

wuraan shih huarnjing yoou duih shengmihng yoouhaih huoh yooudur de wuhzhih.  gongchaang de yanwuh shih yi zhoong wuraan yinweih yoouhaih feihbuh.  yiinyohngshuii 'li de wushuii yee shih yi zhoong wuraan yinweih yoou xihjun her bihngdur shii rern huahnbihng.  gongdih taih duo zaohyin shii fuhjihn de jumirn shimiarn huoh jiinzhang err huahnbihng.

{{BookCat}}

Water pollution is the pollution of water resources such as lakes, rivers, oceans and groundwater. It occurs when pollutants without treatment such as waste from homes, factories and other buildings get into water resources.

shuii wuraan shih shuiiyuarn rur hurpo, herliur, haiiyarng her dihxiahshuii beih wuraan.  meir chuulii'guo de wuraanwuh rur zhuhzhair, gongchaang her qita jiahnzhuhwuh de feiwuh jihnruh shuiiyuarn jiuh huih zaohcherng wuraan.

{{BookCat}}

A '''hazard''' is a natural event that brings about great casualties and economic loss to an area.
{{Robox|theme=4|title=Is it a hazard?}} * A small earthquake bringing no damage is not a hazard as it does not bring damage to humans. * A major volcanic eruption in a remote region with no settlements is not a hazard as it does not bring damage to humans. {{Robox/Close}}
There are several types of hazards: * '''Tectonic hazards''' include earthquakes, volcanic eruptions and tsunamis. * '''Biological hazards''' include locust swarms, epidemics, pandemics... * '''Climatic hazards''' include tropical cyclones, tornadoes, thunderstorms, cold surges, droughts, heat waves... * '''Geologic hazards''' include landslides, mudflows, earthflows, avalanches...
In this chapter, we shall cover tectonic hazards.
{{DSEGeogM1}}

{{FUN-beg|refs2=1|alttitle2=Modifying someone else's content}}
==Retrograding content==
There is a myth that newer Trainz Simulator 12 ({{TL|TS12}}) content cannot be modified to run in an earlier Trainz version. While literally true for Routes and sessions (at least until some 3rd party software engineer tackles the difference between the data models used internally in TS12 and writes a program that translates them), it is not true in the least for unscripted scenery assets and most rolling stock&mdash;even most which contain scripts. A critical examination of the difference between the data elements (tags and containers which are mandatory) a v2.0 ({{TL|TRS2004|TRS2004-SP0}}) asset and v3.7 (TS12) asset have very few differences. Most of those which do occur happen in Texture.txt files using extended graphical function capabilities not present in older Trainz releases.  
{{TRS-sect-stub}}
