====Tribe Rubeae====

=====Genus ''Rubus''=====

======''Rubus'' subg. ''Chamaemorus''======

The native status of "Rubus chamaemorus" in New York could be subject to question. It is a circumboreal bramble, native to all provinces of Canada and present in the states of Alaska, Minnesota, New Hampshire, and Maine. However, the only vouchered report of cloudberry growing outside of cultivation in New York was from Suffolk County, Long Island in 1908.<ref>[http://www.torreybotanical.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Juncus_diffusissimus_NY.pdf Eric E. Lamont and Stephen M. Young (2005) "''Juncus diffusissimus'', an addition to the flora of New York, with notes on its recent spread in the United States." ''The Journal of the Torrey Botanical Society'', '''132(4)''': 635-643. 2005.]</ref>

